.TH QEMATE 1 "March 30, 2026" "Qemate 4.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
qemate \- Hardened QEMU virtual machine manager for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qemate
.I COMMAND
[
.I SUBCOMMAND
] [
.I OPTIONS
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Qemate
is a streamlined command-line utility for managing QEMU virtual machines (VMs). It simplifies VM creation, control, and configuration, leveraging QEMU with KVM acceleration for enhanced performance when supported by the host system.

Version 4.1.0 introduces a significant **Security Hardening Layer**:
.IP \(bu 3
**Hardened Config Lexer**: Replaces standard shell sourcing with a strict regex-based parser and key whitelisting. This prevents arbitrary code execution via modified configuration files.
.IP \(bu 3
**Ownership Enforcement**: Automatically verifies that VM configurations are owned by the current user and enforces strict \fB600\fR file permissions.
.IP \(bu 3
**Pre-flight Validation**: Performs centralized dependency checks for \fBswtpm\fR, \fBvirtiofsd\fR, and \fBsmbd\fR before VM initialization to prevent partial starts and orphaned processes.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B vm
Manage virtual machines.
.RS
.TP
.B create NAME [OPTIONS]
Create a new VM with optimized defaults for Linux or Windows.
.RS
.TP
.B --os-type TYPE
OS preset (\fBlinux\fR|\fBwindows\fR; default: linux).
.TP
.B --memory SIZE
Memory size (e.g., 4G, 2048M).
.TP
.B --cores N
Number of CPU cores (1-64).
.TP
.B --disk-size SIZE
Virtual disk size (e.g., 60G).
.TP
.B --machine TYPE
Machine type (e.g., q35,accel=kvm).
.TP
.B --enable-audio / --no-audio
Enable or disable audio passthrough.
.TP
.B --enable-tpm / --no-tpm
Enable TPM 2.0 emulation (requires \fBswtpm\fR).
.TP
.B --spice / --no-spice
Enable SPICE display server.
.TP
.B --share-backend BACKEND
Select sharing method (\fBauto\fR|\fBvirtfs\fR|\fBsmb\fR|\fBvirtiofs\fR).
.RE
.TP
.B start NAME [OPTIONS]
Start a VM.
.RS
.TP
.B --headless
Start without a graphical console.
.TP
.B --iso PATH
Attach a primary ISO for installation.
.TP
.B --virtio-iso PATH
Attach a secondary ISO (e.g., VirtIO-Win drivers).
.TP
.B --debug
Print the full generated QEMU command to stderr before launching.
.RE
.TP
.B stop NAME [--force]
Stop a VM. \fB--force\fR performs an immediate shutdown.
.TP
.B delete NAME [--force]
Delete a VM and its disk image. \fB--force\fR skips confirmation.
.TP
.B resize NAME SIZE [--force]
Resize the VM disk (e.g., \fB80G\fR or \fB+20G\fR). Includes validation to prevent accidental shrinking. VM must be stopped unless \fB--force\fR is used.
.TP
.B list
List all VMs, their current status, and lock state.
.TP
.B status NAME
Display detailed VM configuration and runtime metrics.
.TP
.B configure NAME SETTING VALUE
Modify VM settings. Supported settings:
.RS
.TP
.B cores
Integer 1\(en64.
.TP
.B memory
e.g. \fB4G\fR, \fB2048M\fR.
.TP
.B audio
\fBon\fR|\fBoff\fR
.TP
.B audio-latency
Output latency in microseconds, e.g. \fB100000\fR.
.TP
.B tpm
\fBon\fR|\fBoff\fR (requires \fBswtpm\fR).
.TP
.B spice
\fBon\fR|\fBoff\fR
.TP
.B spice-port
Port number 1024\(en65535 (default: 5930).
.TP
.B video
\fBvirtio-vga\fR|\fBvirtio-gpu\fR|\fBqxl-vga\fR|\fBqxl\fR|\fBstd\fR|\fBvmware\fR
.TP
.B vram
VRAM size in MiB, 16\(en512.
.TP
.B network-type
\fBuser\fR|\fBpasst\fR|\fBtap\fR|\fBnone\fR
.TP
.B network-model
\fBvirtio-net-pci\fR|\fBe1000\fR|\fBrtl8139\fR
.TP
.B bridge
Host bridge interface name, e.g. \fBbr0\fR (tap mode only).
.TP
.B share-backend
\fBauto\fR|\fBvirtfs\fR|\fBsmb\fR|\fBvirtiofs\fR
.TP
.B --raw
Open the config file directly in \fB$EDITOR\fR (use with caution).
.RE
.RE

.TP
.B share
Manage shared folders.
.RS
.TP
.B add NAME [TAG:]PATH
Add a shared directory. Tag is auto-derived if omitted.
.TP
.B remove NAME TAG
Remove a shared directory by its tag.
.TP
.B list NAME
List all configured shares for the VM.
.RE

.TP
.B usb
Manage USB passthrough.
.RS
.TP
.B add NAME VENDOR:PRODUCT
Attach a host USB device.
.TP
.B remove NAME VENDOR:PRODUCT
Detach a host USB device.
.TP
.B list NAME
List configured USB devices for the VM.
.RE

.TP
.B net
Manage port forwarding rules.
.RS
.TP
.B port add NAME [IP:]HOST:GUEST[:PROTO]
Forward a host port to a guest port. PROTO defaults to \fBtcp\fR.
.TP
.B port remove NAME [IP:]HOST:GUEST[:PROTO]
Remove a port forwarding rule.
.PP
Network type, model, and bridge interface are configured via \fBvm configure\fR.
.RE

.TP
.B security
Manage VM protection.
.RS
.TP
.B lock NAME
Prevent modification or deletion of the VM.
.TP
.B unlock NAME
Allow modification or deletion.
.RE

.SH NETWORK BACKENDS
.TP
.B user
SLiRP userspace NAT. Default; no host setup required.
.TP
.B passt
Unprivileged backend using the host network stack directly. Recommended upgrade from user.
.TP
.B tap
Kernel-accelerated TAP interface. Requires a pre-configured host bridge. Fastest option.
.TP
.B none
No network interface attached to the VM.

.SH SECURITY & CONCURRENCY
Qemate implements strict \fBflock\fR-based locking on configuration files to prevent race conditions during simultaneous CLI commands. The script operates with a \fBumask 0077\fR to ensure all created files are accessible only by the owner.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B QEMATE_VM_DIR
Overrides the default VM storage directory (\fB~/QVMs\fR).
.TP
.B LOG_LEVEL
Sets logging verbosity (\fBDEBUG\fR, \fBINFO\fR, \fBWARNING\fR, \fBERROR\fR; default: INFO).

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/QVMs/VM_NAME/config
Hardened configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/QVMs/VM_NAME/disk.qcow2
Primary QCOW2 disk image.
.TP
.I ~/QVMs/VM_NAME/logs/qemate_vm.log
General execution logs.
.TP
.I ~/QVMs/VM_NAME/logs/error.log
Direct stderr output from the QEMU process.

.SH EXAMPLES
Create and start a Windows 11 VM with TPM and VirtIO drivers:
.EX
qemate vm create win11 --os-type windows --enable-tpm
qemate vm start win11 --iso win11.iso --virtio-iso virtio-win.iso
.EE

Add a high-performance shared folder:
.EX
qemate vm configure myvm share-backend virtiofs
qemate share add myvm /home/user/work
.EE

Switch to passt networking:
.EX
qemate vm configure myvm network-type passt
.EE

Forward a web port:
.EX
qemate net port add myvm 8080:80:tcp
.EE

Tune audio latency:
.EX
qemate vm configure myvm audio-latency 100000
.EE

